Follow the step-by-step tutorial to learn how to sell bitcoins (BTC) in Nigeria and which crypto trading applications you should use. To begin, Main Points to Remember: To sell Bitcoin in Nigeria, you must first sign up for a crypto trading app, which will provide you with a bitcoin wallet address that will allow you to accept and store Bitcoin in Nigeria. You’ll have to analyze several crypto exchanges based on withdrawal and deposit methods and charges, fiat currencies supported, timeliness and other associated fees to find the best application to sell Bitcoin in Nigeria. When trying to sell Bitcoin in Nigeria, here is a list of suggested crypto trading applications to consider: Breet is an over-the-counter (OTC) cryptocurrency trading platform that allows crypto consumers and companies to convert and withdraw bitcoin for cash in less than five minutes with no risk. Breet does not sell Bitcoin in Nigeria through a peer-to-peer exchange. You can simply convert your Bitcoin to cash and withdraw it to your Naira bank account using Breet. There are no withdrawal fees, no third-party fees, and no hidden costs… In Nigeria, selling bitcoin on Breet is completely free. Breet is not limited to just the trade of Bitcoins, you can as well trade Ethereum, Bitcoin Cash, Litecoin, Dogecoins, and more using Breet. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1696547 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Breet-image-2.jpg" alt="" width="936" height="536" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Breet-image-2.jpg 936w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Breet-image-2-320x183.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Breet-image-2-640x366.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Breet-image-2-600x344.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px" /> Binance Binance is a worldwide cryptocurrency exchange software that allows users to trade a wide choice of credible currencies on this well-kno