you can sell and withdraw your Bitcoin. Check out our guide on how to sell Bitcoin on Breet. Sign in and generate a bitcoin wallet address for your own usage after you’ve enrolled with a crypto trading app of your choosing. This bitcoin wallet address may be thought of as a virtual bank account number, with ‘wallet address’ representing the account number and ‘Bitcoin’ representing the bank name. You may receive bitcoin from anywhere using your bitcoin wallet address. Copy the address and transfer it to your bitcoin wallet. Remember to double-check the address before transmitting, otherwise, you might lose your whole Bitcoin. If you’re utilizing a peer-to-peer exchange system, you’ll need to locate a buyer prepared to pay you money for your bitcoin after it’s been successfully sent to your personal bitcoin wallet address in your crypto trading app. However, if you use Breet, you won’t have to look for a buyer since Breet will convert your bitcoin to the flat equal of how much it’s worth in naira. Then you may make a quick withdrawal to your Naira bank account. How you sell bitcoin in Nigeria is mostly determined by your personal preferences. You must conduct a study to determine which crypto trading software is best for you. Some exchanges are quicker and more expensive, while others prefer to employ P2P trading, which is slower. It’s possible that what works for Paul won’t work for Peter. Begin by asking yourself the following questions:   Consider the following factors while selecting a bitcoin trading app:  After you’ve sold Bitcoin, you can withdraw your funds. In terms of security, storing money on an exchange is a horrible idea. If you’ve sold your Bitcoin for fiat money, be sure you know what options you have for getting your money out of the trading app. These may include the following: While withdrawing your cash, there are a few factors to consider. Charges. These might add up over time, so instead of making multiple smaller withdrawals, attempt to withdraw as much money as possible all at once. Limits. Check to see if there are any restrictions on the amount you may withdraw. Crypto trading applications will occasionally enable you to withdraw more money provided you provide more identifying information, such as your address. Handling times It’s critical to be aware of the length of withdrawals. It takes 3-5 working days for bank transfers to be completed. Credit and debit cards are more expensive than cash, but they are significantly faster. Although no one can predict the future, the market may be attentively examined. Look at the overall trends, how Bitcoin has changed in recent weeks and months, and whether any upgrades are on the way, among other things. Follow Bitcoin news in Nigeria to have a better understanding of the cryptocurrency industry and make an informed choice. Take-home point, it is never a good or bad time to buy or sell bitcoins. You are expected to DYOR (Do Your Own Research).